					<description><![CDATA[<p>Glow Becomes A Unicorn With Fresh Funding Cybersecurity startup Glow, based in Israel and the U.S., raised $180M at a $1.2B valuation today, exiting stealth as a unicorn. Sequoia, Cyberstarts,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/glow-raises-180m-to-expand-ai-powered-endpoint-security-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Glow Raises $180M to Expand AI-Powered Endpoint Security Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Glow Becomes A Unicorn With Fresh Funding</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cybersecurity startup Glow, based in Israel and the U.S., raised $180M at a $1.2B valuation today, exiting stealth as a unicorn. Sequoia, Cyberstarts, Greenoaks, and Redpoint Ventures led the round, joined by Index Ventures, Swish Ventures, Lux Capital, Operator Collective and Holly Ventures.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding will boost Glow&#8217;s U.S. Expansion, help grow Glow Labs, a new research arm for the company, and improve the platform&#8217;s AI-native endpoint security capabilities as enterprises demand preventative cyber security more than ever.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded by Roi Tiger, Omer Singer, and Ophir Arie, Glow creates AI-native endpoint protection that analyzes enterprise devices, spots threats in real time, and stops unsafe software, scripts, and AI tools from causing harm.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Adoption Creates New Enterprise Security Risks</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Workplaces adopting AI rapidly have completely rewritten endpoint security, believes Glow. With more workers bringing AI assistants, autonomous agents, plug-ins and software into enterprise workplaces and cyber attackers harnessing AI to find flaws and carry out exploits much faster.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm&#8217;s platform employs bespoke AI agents, who perpetually observe workplace machines from a centralised command-and-control system rather than resident on user devices. They can inspect software for potential behaviours, quantify risks and automatically manage and update security settings without hampering worker efficiency.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We launched the company with the understanding that the age of endpoint security based on reaction is over. Prevention needs to become a more prevalent strategy&#8221; according to Chief Executive OfficerRoi Tiger. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With AI, it has finally become viable to implement this strategy on an enterprise scale; for organizations to understand software behaviors ahead of the next threat emerging, instead of reacting after a </span><a href="https://study.com/academy/lesson/compromise-definition-examples.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">compromise</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has taken place.</span></p>
<h2><b>Platform Focuses On Prevention Instead Of Reaction</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203699" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203699" class="size-full wp-image-203699" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Glow-2.png" alt="Illustration of AI-powered cybersecurity agents using contextual analysis to prevent threats, automatically governing enterprise applications and protecting cloud environments." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203699" class="wp-caption-text">AI-driven preventive cybersecurity is shifting enterprise defence from reactive threat detection to continuous contextual analysis, enabling intelligent application governance and proactive protection across complex digital environments. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Glow’s AI agents use this context to decide whether the applications are permitted or should be blocked automatically. Glow’s platform also avoids relying on single security events and analyses the activity within the broader context of operations to minimise false positives.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has several dozen enterprise clients, including some in the Fortune 500 from sectors including healthcare, retail, and financial services, many of whom are actively using the platform while others are still deploying.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its founders bring a mix of cybersecurity and enterprise software backgrounds including Tiger, who formerly was VP of Engineering at Meta, a co-founder of Onavo, Singer, who previously headed cybersecurity strategy at Snowflake and Arie, who had previously held a research lead at Claroty.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cashea-raises-100m-expand-consumer-credit-venezuela/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cashea Raises $100M to Expand Interest-Free Consumer Credit in Venezuela</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports Research And Global Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Glow plans to deploy the latest funding to scale up its go-to-market across the United States and invest more in R&amp;D at Glow Labs. The organisation will also expand its employee base, with demand for enterprise AI set to boom. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment follows confidence from industry experts, who feel it’s time for organisations to be armed with new kinds of security architecture designed to manage AI native software, rather than simply inspecting existing applications.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As enterprises move away from point security solutions in favour of a wider security strategy, Glow will attempt to establish itself as an end-to-end endpoint security solution created with the era of artificial intelligence in mind.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment follows confidence from the investment community that an AI native, security solution would be important in the security of the enterprises going forwards as autonomy software grows prevalent in enterprises.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
